<subSubSection id="8FC8B2CB7E7EFFECFF6111996BA40780" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C76DE1407E7EFFECFF6111996BA40780" blockId="16.[151,1436,151,487]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="F5A63D527E7EFFECFF6111996E1606D6" bold="true" box="[198,338,151,177]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Discussion.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A3439CB17E7EFFECFEFE11966D2006D5" author="Fulton, S. W. &amp; Grant, F. E." box="[345,612,152,178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="59 - 68" refId="ref28897" refString="Fulton, S. W. &amp; Grant, F. E. (1902) Some little known Victorian Decapod Crustacea with descriptions of new species, no. 2. Proceedings of the Royal Society, Victoria, 15 (1), 59 - 68." type="journal article" year="1902">Fulton &amp; Grant (1902)</bibRefCitation>
placed their new species in 
<taxonomicName id="00D29AC37E7EFFECFC1511966A5D06D5" authority="Stimpson, 1858" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[946,1305,152,178]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5A63D527E7EFFECFC1511966B1306D6" box="[946,1111,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Cryptodromia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A3439CB17E7EFFECFBF911966A5D06D5" author="Stimpson, W." box="[1118,1305,152,178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="225 - 252" refId="ref35789" refString="Stimpson, W. (1858) Prodromus descriptionis animalium evertebratorum quae in Expeditione ad Oceanum Pacificum Septentrionalem, a Republica Federata missa, Cadwaladaro Ringgold et Johanne Rodgers ducibus, observavit et descripsit W. Stimpson Pars VII. Crustacea Anomoura. Proceedings of the Academy of natural Science of Philadelphia, 10 (4), 225 - 252 (63 - 90)." type="journal article" year="1858">Stimpson, 1858</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, before the generic definition was revised. 
<bibRefCitation id="A3439CB17E7EFFECFDB011B06DB406BF" author="Borradaile, L. A." box="[535,752,190,216]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="297 - 303" refId="ref27157" refString="Borradaile, L. A. (1903) On the genera of the Dromiidae. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (7), 11, 297 - 303." type="journal article" year="1903">Borradaile (1903)</bibRefCitation>
made an important addition to generic characters in the 
<taxonomicName id="00D29AC37E7EFFECFF3011EB6E5F0698" authorityName="de Haan" authorityYear="1833" box="[151,283,229,255]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dromiidae</taxonomicName>
when he stated that a cheliped epipod is absent in 
<taxonomicName id="00D29AC37E7EFFECFC3811EB6B090699" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[927,1101,229,254]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5A63D527E7EFFECFC3811EB6B090699" box="[927,1101,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Cryptodromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but present in 
<taxonomicName id="00D29AC37E7EFFECFAAB11EB6E160741" authority="Stimpson, 1858" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Petalomera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5A63D527E7EFFECFAAB11EB6AD80699" box="[1292,1436,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Petalomera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A3439CB17E7EFFECFF3010026E160741" author="Stimpson, W." box="[151,338,268,294]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="225 - 252" refId="ref35789" refString="Stimpson, W. (1858) Prodromus descriptionis animalium evertebratorum quae in Expeditione ad Oceanum Pacificum Septentrionalem, a Republica Federata missa, Cadwaladaro Ringgold et Johanne Rodgers ducibus, observavit et descripsit W. Stimpson Pars VII. Crustacea Anomoura. Proceedings of the Academy of natural Science of Philadelphia, 10 (4), 225 - 252 (63 - 90)." type="journal article" year="1858">Stimpson, 1858</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Applying this new definition Rathbun (1923) changed the Australian species to 
<taxonomicName id="00D29AC37E7EFFECFAAB10026AD00742" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[1292,1428,268,293]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Petalomera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5A63D527E7EFFECFAAB10026AD00742" box="[1292,1428,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Petalomera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this was never correct because it lacked the essential defining feature of this genus, having petaloid meri on the first two pairs of pereopods. Finally in his revision of 
<taxonomicName id="00D29AC37E7EFFECFC2010576B910714" authority=", McLay (1993)" authorityName="McLay" authorityYear="1993" box="[903,1237,345,371]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Petalomera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5A63D527E7EFFECFC2010576B500715" box="[903,1044,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Petalomera</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A3439CB17E7EFFECFB8210576B910714" author="McLay, C. L." box="[1061,1237,345,371]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="111 - 251" refId="ref31531" refString="McLay, C. L. (1993) Crustacea Decapoda: The sponge crabs (Dromiidae) of New Caledonia and the Philippines with a review of the genera. In: Crosnier, A. (ed.), Resultats des Campagnes MUSORSTOM, vol. 10. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle (Paris), 156, 111 - 251." type="journal article" year="1993">McLay (1993)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
transferred it to 
<taxonomicName id="00D29AC37E7EFFECFF30108E6FB507FE" authorityName="McLay" authorityYear="1993" box="[151,241,384,409]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5A63D527E7EFFECFF30108E6FB507FE" box="[151,241,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Dromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but not without some misgivings. The comparison of larval characters by Lim and Ng (2001), which was based on groupings of species on the basis of adult characters by 
<bibRefCitation id="A3439CB17E7EFFECFC5210A86BED07A7" author="McLay, C. L." box="[1013,1193,422,448]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="111 - 251" refId="ref31531" refString="McLay, C. L. (1993) Crustacea Decapoda: The sponge crabs (Dromiidae) of New Caledonia and the Philippines with a review of the genera. In: Crosnier, A. (ed.), Resultats des Campagnes MUSORSTOM, vol. 10. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle (Paris), 156, 111 - 251." type="journal article" year="1993">McLay (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, showed that it was apparent that 
<taxonomicName id="00D29AC37E7EFFECFE9110C36D730781" authorityName="Fulton &amp; Grant" authorityYear="1902" box="[310,567,461,486]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wilsoni">
<emphasis id="F5A63D527E7EFFECFE9110C36D730781" box="[310,567,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Cryptodromia wilsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
did not belong in 
<taxonomicName id="00D29AC37E7EFFECFCAA10C36C230781" authorityName="McLay" authorityYear="1993" box="[781,871,461,486]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5A63D527E7EFFECFCAA10C36C230781" box="[781,871,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Dromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and thus deserved a new genus.
</paragraph>
